In continuation of its rebuilding process ahead of the 2023 general election, the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, national reconciliation and strategy committee is currently meeting with former governors elected on the platform of the party. The committee chairman and immediate President of the Senate, Dr Bukola Saraki arrived at the Legacy House, Presidential campaign headquarters of the party at exactly 12:50 PM local time alongside other members of the committee. On the ground for the meeting at the time of filing this report are Senator Saraki, former Anambra state governor, Peter Obi, immediate past Kwara state governor, and erstwhile governor of Kwara state, Abdulfatai Ahmed. Others included Ibrahim Shema, Boni Haruna, Ahmed Makarfi, Gabriel Suswam, Sam Egwu, Emmanuel Uduaghan, Ramalan Yero, Babangida Aliyu, Ibrahim Idris, Wada Idris, and Liyel Imoke, former governors of Katsina, Adamawa, Kaduna, Benue, Ebonyi, Delta, Kaduna, Niger,Â  and Cross River states respectively. The Saraki-led committee has been interfacing with its top stalwarts in recent times amidst unconfirmed reports of possible defection into the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC. Vanguard News Nigeria An emergency National Executive Committee (NEC)Meeting of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is ongoing at the party's national secretariat, Wadata Plaza, Abuja. April 19, 2018 In "News" The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, is currently holding its 81st National Executive Committee, NEC, meeting at its national secretariat, Wadata Plaza, Abuja. November 29, 2018 In "News" It has been a very busy and hectic period for the National Organising Secretary, but one striking consolation is that it is a period of Naira rain for the PDP, a period a former National Chairman of the party would say Oja Ata. November 1, 2014 In "Politics"